title: Never Ape an Ape Man
description: The gang is hired by Daphne's uncle, a famous director, as extras in his latest project. But the star of the show is a real nasty ape.

title: Battle of the Humungonauts
description: A pair of brutal gargantuas begin breaking apart the town, which sadly mirrors the fractured relationship of Mystery Inc. See, while searching for Shaggy, Scooby accidentally discovers him canoodling with Velma. Feeling betrayed, Scooby is inconsolable despite the best efforts of Fred and Daphne to cheer him up and put the team back together. Although they ultimately reunite to capture and defeat the Humongonauts, the rift in the gang is deep and the question by the end of the episode soon becomes can Mystery Inc. ever be healed again?

title: Attack of the Weird Al-Osaurus!
description: Driving through the Rocky Mountains, the Mystery Inc. gang discovers a sleep-away accordion camp run by none other than Weird Al Yankovic! But there is no accordion joy when a horrible dinosaur attacks the camp. Can our heroes and Weird Al solve this prehistoric mystery or are they destined to become dino-food?

title: What the Hex Is Going On?
description: When the gang visits the Weatherby estate, they must investigate a mysterious voice and a ghost who demands the family return its fortune to a neighboring clan.

title: Revenge of the Swamp Monster!
description: Scooby-Doo and the Mystery Inc. gang meet up with basketball legend and bowling aficionado Chris Paul at a golf tournament fundraiser held in Florida. Shaggy's come to caddy for Mr. Paul and help him with this game so the Assist King can save a local school from going under. But, when a horrible Swamp Monster attacks trying to destroy the charity event, our heroes and Mr. Paul must finish the tournament and save the school, and possibly their own lives!

title: Come Undone
description: It's the end of the world! And our heroes must work together to ultimately realize their love for each other is the true Heart of the Jaguar.

title: The Secret of the Ghost Rig
description: A mysterious ghost trucker is terrorizing Crystal Cove. Add to that all the doorknobs have begun to disappear from around town, someone has hidden a priceless diamond and Fred's dad, the Mayor, is up for re-election against a guy named Avocados. Scooby and the gang have their hands full. Oh, and did we mention Daphne has been set-up on a blind date with a pinhead named Rung Ladderton, who - wait for it - sells ladders for a living.

title: Dance of the Undead
description: When Crystal Cove's favorite southern celebrity chef has a cooking accident, strange incidents ensue.

title: Scooby-Doo and the Sky Town Cool School!
description: Scooby-Doo and the gang arrive at a mountaintop cool school run by none other than famous actor Billy Dee Williams. They're here to learn how to be cool, and Mr. Williams is the smooth-tongued professor of suave. But, the gang loses their cool when an angry pterodactyl monster keeps attacking them and the school trying to scare everyone away. But, Billy Dee has extra cool to spare, and he and the gang work together to get to the bottom of this kooky mystery before it's too late.

title: Eating Crow
description: The gang enters the heart of the American Gothic South in order to help an attractive farmer who Fred wants to impress with his mystery-solving prowess. A horrifying Scarecrow has come to life and attempts to drive everyone off his farm.

title: Dance Matron of Mayhem!
description: When famous dancer Maddie Ziegler wins an old, haunted dance studio in a competition, she asks her friend Daphne Blake and her mystery solving friends to help her investigate the place. They soon run afoul of the ghost of Madame Zobrinsky, famous original owner of the dance studio in question. Does Maddie have the dance skills to teach our Shaggy and Scooby to be graceful and light on their feet?

title: Hollywood Knights!
description: When Scooby and the gang are investigating one of the most haunted mansions in the historic Hollywood Hills, they meet up with none-other than famous actor George Takei. His house is next door, and he's hoping to save this abandoned, old mansion as a historic landmark. As an old suit of armor comes alive and chases them all over the spooky estate, the gang and Mr. Takei discover the mansion is not as abandoned as everyone thought.

title: Haunted House Hang-Up
description: The gang investigates a haunted southern mansion when the Mystery Machine overheats and strands them nearby.

title: The Grasp of the Gnome
description: The Royal Knights Faire has come to Crystal Cove and the whole gang is in attendance. Unfortunately, so is a scary gnome who has begun attacking and paralyzing guests. Specifically, guests who are wearing pirate costumes. The gang decides to help trap the gnome. But when Shaggy, who is dressed as a pirate along with Scooby, is captured by the frightening little beast, it quickly becomes a race against time to find him or Scooby could lose his best buddy forever.

title: Heart of Evil
description: Dr. Zin, of Jonny Quest fame, wreaks havoc on Crystal Cove.

title: Mysteries on the Disorient Express
description: Unhappy about a mystery free, three day, cross-country train trip with the gang, Fred is pleasantly surprised to discover a monster mystery on board. He's less pleasantly surprised when that mystery is interrupted by a second mystery, then a third, then a fourth…

title: A Haunt of a Thousand Voices!
description: When Daphne takes the rest of the gang to meet her friend, famous voice over actor Frank Welker, they inadvertently find themselves in the middle of a very strange mystery full of several different monsters and several different actors! The gang meets voice over actors Frank Welker, Grey DeLisle-Griffin, Matthew Lillard and Kate Micucci, who have all gathered to do their job of recording an episode of a hit animated show that vaguely seems to be about four teenagers and their talking animal. But, when different monsters show up and start abducting various actors from the group, it looks like our gang has a real mystery on their hands, even more mysterious than how the actors' voices all sound strangely familiar to our gang.

title: Ollie Ollie In-Come Free!
description: When our mystery solving gang agrees to help Ricky Gervais with a haunted antique Egyptian statue of a cat, they find themselves embroiled in a confrontation with the ancient goddess Bast in mummy form!

title: Trading Chases
description: Fred switches places with Jeff, the tour guide at a history museum, to give him a chance to lead the gang in solving a mystery. The mystery: a frightening Egyptian crocodile deity is terrorizing the museum. The problem: Fred is instantly jealous of this new guy and sets out to solve the mystery before he can, using Jeff's tour group of children!

title: The Legend of Alice May
description: There's a new girl at Crystal Cove High named Alice May and she's set her romantic sights on Fred. Only one problem, Alice is dead! That's right, Fred's new girlfriend is a dead girl. Alice is a ghost, famous for snatching up guys like Fred and disappearing with them forever. Now, she wants to take Fred to the prom, which means he's next. Fortunately, Daphne also wants to go to the prom with Fred and she's not going to let Alice beat her to the "punch" bowl (wink-wink). And what about the rest of the gang? Well, they've got problems of their own. See, Velma wants to go the prom with Shaggy but Scooby wants Shaggy to watch a Vincent Van Ghoul marathon with him. You keeping up? Good because this one is going to get nasty and when it's over, Scooby and the gang will never be the same again.

title: In Fear of the Phantom
description: Velma's favorite band, the Hex Girls, is in town and the gang has a front row seat. Unfortunately, so does an evil specter named The Phantom, who wants the Hex Girls out of the music business permanently! Solution? Send Daphne undercover as Crush, the newest member of the band. But when she's nabbed by the Phantom, Fred goes into freakout mode finally realizing he actually has feelings for Daphne. Meanwhile, Scooby and Shaggy are having their own problems due to Shaggy spending too much time with Velma. His solution: replace Shaggy with a puppet.

title: The Night the Clown Cried II: Tears of Doom
description: Crybaby Clown is back with a vengeance. He's kidnapping all sorts of folks all over Crystal Cove - namely a therapist, a hairdresser, a plastic surgeon and a publicist!

title: Jeepers It's the Creeper
description: The kids look for a ghostly bank robber, who seems able to walk through walls.

title: The Norse Case Scenario
description: The gang goes on a camping trip. Fred's desire for the gang to get in touch with their natural instincts and hones their mystery skills turns into on-the-job training as Viking Ghosts attack and attempt to drive them away or worse.

title: Too Many Dummies!
description: When Scooby and the gang are hired to escort a supposedly possessed ventriloquist dummy to the annual Ventriloquist Talent Competition, they meet up with the two judges of the competition, Jeff Dunham and Darci Lynne Farmer. True to form, the supposedly possessed dummy turns out to be terribly-and-horribly-possessed! It comes alive and attacks the competition!

title: Where There's a Will, There's a Wraith
description: It's a classic haunted house caper when a rich man, whose life Scooby once saved, writes Scooby into his will!  Now, to collect his share of the fortune the gang must spend a night in a creepy mansion along with the rich man's kooky relatives and, worse, a spooky phantom!

title: The Tao of Scoob!
description: Scooby-Doo takes the gang to meet his good friend, Lucy Liu, at her art gallery in Queens. She has a large art studio above the gallery that she uses to paint and sculpt. She's having a big gallery opening, but when one of her large humanoid modern sculptures comes alive and attacks them, the gang and Lucy have a real mystery on their hands. It seems the monster is very interested in an old seemingly-worthless piece of wood Ms. Liu collected when she was a girl right here in Queens. It turns out that it's actually a puzzle-box and what it contains opens up a whole new layer to this mystery. Can our gang help Lucy Liu save her gallery opening and trap the monster? Or will they all be painted into a corner, permanently!

title: There Wolf
description: The gang rushes Scooby to an animal hospital when he suddenly falls ill. Things go from bad to worse when they discover the Gothic, old hospital is also home to a rampaging werewolf.

title: All Paws on Deck
description: The gang climb aboard the cruise ship run by Fred's cousin, despite Velma's strong dislike of water. But a water phobia is the least of their problems when a terrifying sea monster attacks the ship!

title: Screama Donna
description: To solve the mystery of a ghostly performer haunting her former venue, the gang has to pretend to be a rock band themselves! But can they solve the case before Velma has to actually get on stage and sing?

title: Elementary, My Dear Shaggy!
description: When Scooby and the gang are taking a tour of merry old London, they run afoul of horrible screaming skulls of English legend! They team up with an eccentric man who claims to be none other than Sherlock Holmes. Of course, he can't be the real thing, can he?

title: The Dragon's Secret
description: After an exchange student named Mai Lee shows up in town to stay with Velma, strange Kung Fu wizards begin attacking the town trying to get her.

title: The Feast of Dr. Frankenfooder!
description: When Shaggy and Scooby are excited to visit a scary haunted old castle in Germany, the rest of the gang are confused until they meet up with none other than famous chef, writer and TV presenter Alton Brown! Shaggy, Scooby and Alton are good friends (mostly because they will happily eat any experimental scientific food experiment Alton comes up with). Alton Brown is on the trail of his ancestor, mad scientist Dr. Cornelius Frankenfooder! It's said he made a crazy Monster from animated foodstuffs that haunts this old castle to this day. Mr. Brown has to get to the bottom of this familial mystery. Obviously our gang is on board to help. "Come for the kooky scientific food creations. Stay for the horrible monster!"

title: Ghost in the Mystery Machine
description: Fred's worst nightmare comes true when an evil spirit possesses the Mystery Machine and turns his beloved van into an unrelenting monster out to destroy him and the gang before they can solve the mystery.

title: I Scooby Dooby Do
description: The gang is honored to take part in the wedding of two close friends. But can Best Man Shaggy and Maid of Honor Daphne save their friend's perfect day before it's ruined by a Ghost Bride bent on destroying everyone else's happily ever after?

title: Scary Christmas
description: It's Christmas Eve and Fred is ready to solve a Christmas mystery! Unfortunately the town the gang has arrived in is being attacked by a Pterodactyl and it doesn't seem to have anything to do with Christmas!

title: The Night the Clown Cried
description: With the gang split up, Crystal Cove is being tormented by an evil-man-baby called Crybaby Clown!

title: Cher, Scooby and the Sargasso Sea!
description: Scooby-Doo and the gang are hitching a ride with their friend Cher on her yacht coming back from the Azores to the Caribbean. They run "aground" in the strange Sargasso Sea full of thick Sargassum seaweed and a graveyard of old ships of all kinds. When sharkmen start attacking the yacht and all on board, it's up to our gang to team up with Cher and get to the bottom of this murky mystery. Can they escape the sharkmen long enough to dive the wrecks below and find the answers they need?

title: A Clue for Scooby-Doo
description: Scooby and the gang become mixed up in a mystery when he surfs into what appears to be the ghost of Captain Cutler.

title: The Dreaded Remake of Jekyll & Hyde!
description: Scooby and our mystery solving gang are on set with famous singer, dancer, comedian and actress Sandy Duncan. She's back at Mammoth Studios (where our gang first met her) because they're at it again. They're making a remake of the original Jekyll & Hyde movie that Sandy starred in and where Daphne stepped in as Ms. Duncan's stunt double. It seems everything is going well until the same thing happens all over again. A real monster Jekyll starts showing up and causing mayhem, kidnapping actors and scaring everyone away. Can Sandy Duncan and our mystery solving gang survive this savage new Jekyll monster and solve the movie mystery? Even harder, can they survive the angry, emotional movie director!?

title: When the Cicada Calls
description: Bugs are taking over Crystal Cove and attacking some of its most prominent citizens. With Mystery Inc. back together as a team, they begin to investigate and discover all of the attacks have been on employees of a company called Destroido that makes Shaggy and Scooby's favorite snack food - Granma Moonbeams Nature Slivers. Somebody or something wants the company shut down. But when the gang gets too close to the truth, they become the bug's newest target. Of course, the timing couldn't be worse because this just happens to be the moment Fred has decided to make his move on Daphne and finally ask her out. That ain't gonna happen, though, if there are a bunch of bugs trying to kill them.

title: Omelettes Are Forever
description: The gang gets caught up in international espionage and intrigue when they cross paths with British secret agent, Jenny Vex, and must help her complete her dangerous mission of stopping a monstrous, evil mercenary called Minus from killing the meal of breakfast - forever.

title: Mystery 101
description: Velma's got an interview at the prestigious Kingston University, the most selective school in the country. The only catch? The dean wants her and the rest of the Scooby gang to figure out why the ghost of Elias Kingston, the school's founder, is haunting Kingston's book-filled halls!

title: Greece Is the Word
description: We travel back to Ancient Greece, where the gang plays unique roles in a Greek Mystery involving the mythological spider woman, Arachne, and her attempts to disrupt the royal wedding that would unite two great cities.

title: Giant Problems
description: Daphne brings the gang to Ireland to visit an ancient Blake family castle. As the gang becomes enchanted by the magical emerald isle, an angry, rampaging giant makes them reconsider just how wonderful all the old myths and legends really are.

title: All Fear the Freak
description: The mystery comes to a close. The Scooby gang finally gets to the bottom of what happened to the original Mystery Incorporated and why they disappeared.

title: Escape from Mystery Manor
description: The gang investigates the disappearance of the original Mystery Inc. gang.

title: Scooby-Doo and a Mummy, Too
description: The gang helps a professor set up an ancient Egypt exhibit but the star of the display keeps vanishing.

title: The Devouring
description: When a Gluten Demon rises up and attacks famous foodie Francilee Jackson, our gang has to try to stop this monster before it consumes all the bread, pasta and other tasty foodstuffs in Crystal Cove.

title: Scroogey Doo
description: The Scooby Gang enter Dickens' classic "A Christmas Carol" as they try to get to the bottom of the mysterious ghost tormenting Scrooge in 1843 England. Unfortunately, the Ghosts of Christmas Past, Present and Yet To Come begin to convince Velma she's on a disastrous path of her own.

title: The Cursed Cabinet of Professor Madds Markson!
description: When our mystery solving gang accepts the invitation to spend one night in the haunted Savannah Hotel in Las Vegas before its controlled demolition, they find that they're not alone. Famous magicians and entertainers Penn and Teller have also accepted the challenge. The winner gets a million bucks. While the loser may not make it out alive because the place is cursed and haunted by the ghost of infamous illusionist Professor Madds Markson and his horrible monster!

title: Halloween
description: In a strange town the gang tries to convince Fred he's mistaken in his firm belief that you can't solve a mystery on Halloween. When an evil witch appears and frightens the town into calling off Halloween, the gang learns this isn't Fred's first run-in with this witch and the true story behind Fred's feelings about Halloween.

title: Be Quiet Scooby-Doo!
description: To solve the mystery of a creepy crystal crawler, a bat-like cave monster, the gang must venture into the Crystal Canopy, a labyrinth of intricate crystal formations. To make things worse, they can't speak a word while in the Canopy because even the slightest sound will bring the crystals crashing down around them!

title: Theater of Doom
description: Life imitates art in Crystal Cove's annual Haunted Historical Pageant.

title: The Wedding Witch of Wainsly Hall!
description: Scooby and our gang of mystery solving teens have been invited by famous comedian Jeff Foxworthy to help him move an old mansion that he's just purchased. But, when they find out the mansion is haunted by the ghost of an old witch, this Southern-fried mystery takes a dramatic turn. Can our gang help Mr. Foxworthy save this mansion from destruction?

title: Renn Scare
description: The gang heads to Velma's beloved authentic Renaissance Faire, where they must find a way to infiltrate the royal feast in order to stop an evil court jester from ending the king's reign, permanently, and closing the faire.

title: The Curse of Kaniaku
description: On a trip to Japan to visit Velma's friend, the gang comes face to face with the ancient crab monster Kaniaku. They attempt to solve a 700 year-old mystery; meanwhile Daphne accidentally becomes a viral media sensation in Japan.

title: Naughty or Ice
description: Daphne brings the gang to a fancy Ice Hotel co-owned by her family where a new exhibit of ice age artifacts is opening. Things heat up, however, when a frozen Ice Man thaws out and goes on a rampage inside the hotel. Solving the mystery becomes even more complicated when the gang realizes Daphne may just have ulterior motives for going to the hotel to begin with.

title: The Siren's Song
description: Velma is feeling like a fifth wheel. Fred has Daphne and Shaggy has Scooby. Who does she have?

title: Professor Huh? Part 1
description: Fred and the gang are called in to help with a mystery involving a figure from Fred's past, Professor Huh? Fred discovers, Rose, his old childhood friend, with whom he learned mystery solving until they had a falling out, has also arrived with her gang. The race to see which gang could solve the mystery first is on, as the rest of the gang learns there's more to this story than meets the eye and Fred's interest in finding Professor Huh? is as personal as it gets.

title: Scarebear
description: The mayor of Crystal Cove has his camping trip ruined by the evil Scarebear and the gang is on the case.

title: Vote Velma
description: When the ghost of a small town's founder returns to scare off mayoral candidates, the gang decides to run Velma as mayor to bait the ghost. They quickly discover however, that Velma lacks the skill set to make her a popular politician.

title: Dark Night of the Hunters
description: Searching for the Heart of the Jaguar, the Mystery Incorporated gang heads down south of the border.

title: Scooby-Doo! Camp Scare
description: Welcome to Camp Little Moose where the counselors are friendly, the activities are endless and the urban legends are intense. In fact, every time someone tells a ghost story, the creepy creature comes to life!

title: Bedlam in the Big Top
description: A ghost clown haunts a small circus, using hypnotism to bend locals to his will.

title: Gremlin on a Plane
description: The Gang has seats on the largest airplane ever to fly the open airways! Unfortunately the plane is also beset by a Gremlin bent on sabotaging the flight! The Gang has to step up to solve the airborne mystery as well as deal with something even scarier: Daphne flying a plane!

title: Area 51 Adjacent
description: Daphne always dreamed of meeting extra terrestrial life but that dream becomes a nightmare when the gang gets caught up in the mystery of a scary Alien Monster and brought to Area 53, a government facility so secret, it's two numbers higher than Area 51!

title: Scooby-Doo on Zombie Island
description: The Scooby-Doo Mystery gang reunite and visit Moonscar Island, a remote island with a dark secret. Daphne wants more than just a villain in a costume and they get more than they ever expected.

title: Scooby-Doo and the Legend of the Vampire
description: On vacation in Australia, Scooby-Doo and the gang attend a music festival held at Vampire Rock. But the music goes flat when the gang learns that a legendary Australian creature called the Yowie Yahoo is kidnapping the musical acts and turning them into vampires!

title: The Sword, the Fox, and the Scooby Doo!
description: When our mystery solving gang is driving in Japan, they are stopped by none-other than famous actor Mark Hamill. He's in town for a high school reunion, but a terrible Fox Monster has attacked the reunion and kidnapped one of Mark's favorite old teachers. From reliving high school rivalries to surviving haunted, abandoned temples, Mark Hamill and our gang must face a ghastly Fox Monster in order to not only save the day, but their own lives.

title: The People vs. Fred Jones
description: Fred is on trial, accused of being the real mastermind behind all the mysteries he's solved. With the help of his defense attorney, Daphne, we go back over the day's events in a town that had been abandoned since the 1950s because of a toxic chemical spill where a toxic mutant has been terrorizing all who dare go near the town.

title: Stand and Deliver
description: A dandy, well-groomed, 18th century Englishman haunts the highways of Crystal Cove.

title: The Last Inmate!
description: Scooby Doo and the gang are investigating mysterious ghost sightings at an old haunted prison that's been abandoned and derelict for over a hundred years. The Cheever State Penitentiary outside Cleveland, Ohio, has been closed since the 1930s, but it's said to be one of the most haunted places on earth. On the trail of a scary ghost, our gang accidentally bumps into none other than Morgan Freeman who's here making a documentary about the place. When the ghost attacks, our gang and Mr. Freeman team up to solve this mystery. All the while, Mr. Freeman does a documentary with narration regarding our gang and how they solve the mystery in something of a combination "Nature Documentary," "True Crime" and our mystery solving gang in their natural habitat.

title: The Fastest Fast Food Fiend!
description: When Scooby and Shaggy compete in a fast food eating competition sponsored by the Doc Tally restaurant chain, they meet their ultimate challenge eating against none other than comedian Jim Gaffigan! And there's a horrible monster trying to stop the whole contest from finishing. Can Shaggy, Scooby and our mystery solving gang team up with Jim Gaffigan to save the fast food competition, and themselves?

title: The Legend of the Gold Microphone!
description: Joseph "Run" Simmons (aka Reverend Run) originally of Run DMC is opening a hip-hop youth center in Harlem where he hopes to give kids a chance to explore all the powerful sides of Hip-Hop culture. Being huge fans, Shaggy and Scooby have brought the rest of the gang to the grand opening. But, they're not alone. The ghost of a famous bandleader from the 1930s is haunting the youth center, which is located on the spot of the famous old Athena Supper Club. Our mystery teens work with Rev Run to get to the bottom of this mystery, find the legendary golden microphone lost over eighty years ago and get the youth center back up and running.

title: Lost Soles of Jungle River!
description: Scooby-Doo and our gang of mystery solvers travel up a lost river in the Amazon Rainforest with famous comedian and actor Jason Sudeikis in search of a great treasure, the very first high-top sneaker ever made. It's rumored to be in a lost shoe factory from 1912 that used organic rubber to make its shoes. But the gang and Mr. Sudeikis are being stalked by a horrible Snake Man Monster that seems intent upon stopping them from reaching their destination. Can our gang survive this adventure and solve this sneaker-filled mystery? Can Mr. Sudeikis truly find the very first high-top ever made? Can Scooby-Doo find sneakers that actually fit all four feet?!

title: Scooby-Doo and the Loch Ness Monster
description: Scooby-Doo and the Mystery Inc. travel to Scotland to visit Daphne's relatives at Blake Castle, which is situated on Loch Ness, home of the legendary creature who has recently been stalking Daphne's cousin Fiona.

title: The Song of Mystery
description: A hideous creature named Que Horrifico is turning the children of Crystal Cove in to monsters. The adults in the town are in shock, reacting in the only way they know how, by abandoning their children and running away like cowards. Only Scooby and the gang stay behind to solve the mystery. Going undercover as a family - "Dad" Fred, "Mom" Daphne, "Grandma" Velma, "Son" Shaggy and "Baby" Scooby - the gang rents a house in order to capture Que Horrifico. But when their plan backfires and Que Horrifico uses his power over the monster children to cause them to attack the gang, it looks like all is lost. That is until a cartoon character named Broccoli Head comes to their rescue.

title: Mystery Mask Mix-Up
description: When Daphne innocently buys a mask that once belonged to an ancient warlord, the gang finds itself pursued by zombies and ghosts.

title: Night of the Upsetting Shorts
description: The gang heads to Shaggy's beloved grandmother's Florida retirement home, where they learn a crazed Ape Man has been frightening the elderly residents. In order to lessen Shaggy's worry that he doesn't give his Grammy enough bragging rights, the gang pretends Shaggy is their leader and Daphne, his adoring girlfriend, inadvertently putting more pressure on Shaggy to solve the mystery of the Ape Man - who, as it turns out, is less horrifying than the shorts Fred decided to wear to beat the Florida heat.

title: Returning of the Key Ring!
description: When the gang does brunch with Daphne's longtime friend, famous actor Sean Astin, the only mystery on their mind is how to split the check. But their attempts to return a lost set of keys quickly leads them into a genuine mystery at a giant hardware store involving a terrifying force of nature, a monstrous green man! Can Sean Astin and our gang get to the bottom of this green-fingered mystery and return the keys before it's too late?

title: Where Walks Aphrodite
description: Love has come to Crystal Cove. Love in the form of an evil woman by the name of Aphrodite.

title: Pawn of Shadows
description: The Scooby gang is getting close to finally unraveling what happened to the original Mystery Incorporated kids.

title: The Horrible Haunted Hospital of Dr. Phineas Phrag!
description: When investigating a haunted old hospital, Scooby Doo and the gang meet up with actor and comedian Kristen Schaal. The gang happily invites her to be a part of their mystery solving group, and she's ecstatic. She tags along with our gang helping them solve the mystery of the horrible ghost of Dr. Phineas Phrag. More genetically enhanced monster than man, he's been lurking in this hospital since it closed down in the 1950s, and he threatens to destroy any trespassers who dare set foot in these creepy old wards. Can our gang and Ms. Schaal discover the truth of this haunted hospital before it's too late? More importantly, can Kristen Schaal find out how she best fits into our group? So many fun choices - so little time!

title: Poodle Justice
description: It's Scooby's dream come true as the gang visits the set of his favorite TV show and he meets the star, his celebrity crush, a dog actress who plays a detective on the screen. Now all Scooby has to do is work up the courage to actually talk to her while also solving the mystery of the monstrous gargoyle attacking the production!

title: Pizza O'Possum's/The Curse of Half-Beard's Booty
description: Pizza O'Possum's: Shaggy drags the gang to a childhood arcade where he's determined to finally collect enough tickets to win the prize he's wanted since he was a boy. Unfortunately, the animatronic mascot of the place has apparently come to life and has other ideas./The Curse of Half-Beard's Booty: At a seafood restaurant, the gang comes across Captain Cutler, who Fred is determined to catch once and for all. Cutler explains that he's turned over a new leaf and opened up this restaurant to earn an honest living. Unfortunately, the ghost of a legendary pirate, Half-Beard, has been scaring away his customers. Fred and Cutler form an uneasy alliance as he joins the gang on a treasure hunt at Double-Cross Cove where Half-Beard's treasure is supposedly buried.

title: Some Fred Time
description: The gang force the over-worked Fred to relax and take time off from mysteries at Daphne's family's beach house. Unfortunately, when a walking shark attacks the ritzy beach community, the gang is forced to solve the mystery without Fred finding out about it.

title: Mine Your Own Business
description: The gang explores a mining town and investigate a phantom miner, who's driving the business away from a nearby dude ranch.

title: Night Fright
description: Scooby and Shaggy win a dinner date with their hero, Vincent Van Ghoul.

title: The High School Wolfman's Musical Lament!
description: When our mystery solving gang teams up with famous actor Christian Slater, they find themselves embroiled in a musical mystery full of songs, clues and crazy chases. Christian's classmates are having a redo prom to make up for the one they were deprived of when a horrible Wolfman appeared all those years ago. The Wolfman is making a mysterious reappearance at this do-over prom threatening to not only destroy the prom yet again but the lives of all concerned!

title: Scooby-Doo and the Witch's Ghost
description: When the gang meets up with famous fright-writer Ben Ravencroft, he invited them to New England for his hometown's bit Autumn Harvest Festival. Things take a supernatural detour when they learn the place is haunted by Ben's ancestor Sarah! Will the mystery reveal that Sarah was a good-hearted healer or a spell-casting witch? Before you can say, "Scooby Snacks", the gang is on the case tangling with bumbling mummies, monster turkeys and (zoinks) a ghostly secret hidden in the Ravencroft family's past! Grooving to the tunes of the movie's rocking band The Hex Girls, it's Scooby-Doo at his spellbinding, spine-tingling, super-sleuthing best!

title: Attack of the Headless Horror
description: Fred's favorite adventurer, Rick Spartan, has come to town to take over the school's biology class.

title: Beware the Beast from Below
description: Crystal Cove may be the most haunted town in the world but that doesn't stop Scooby and the gang from trying to prove that most of its most famous tourist attractions were fakes, much to the anger and dwindling profits of their parents. But when a radioactive barrel is accidentally opened releasing a hideous sewer beast that cocoons its victims in frozen yogurt, their mystery-solving skills are put to the test. After all, what could a sewer beast, a delicious edible dessert, underground caves and shrimping boats made of balloons possibly have in common? I'll give you a little hint - the local bank.

title: House of the Nightmare Witch
description: A Russian museum exhibit comes to life. It's an evil Russian witch by the name of Baba Yaga. The gang hunts Baba Yaga in Crystal Cove's Haunted Forest of Doom only to end up being the hunted.

title: Decoy for a Dognapper
description: Scooby impersonates a prize-winning Great Dane to catch whoever is stealing show dogs.

title: The Secret Serum
description: There's a vampire loose in the town terrorizing the residents and stealing an odd assortment of loot. When the gang does some sniffing around, they discover an unlikely suspect - Daphne's mother. Things are already strained within Mystery Inc. and with this latest blow, the gang is truly torn in half. Girls on one side, boys on the other. Although they solve the mystery in the end, the rift in Mystery Inc. is now complete. They are a team no more.

title: Falling Star Man!
description: Driving outside Shreveport, Louisiana, our gang of mystery solvers is run off the road by a shooting star that crashes down in the middle of the large ranch belonging to none-other than famous football hall of famer and TV sports host, Terry Bradshaw! Upon further investigation, the "shooting star" turns out to be a spaceship unleashing an alien monster on the local countryside! The gang and Mr. Bradshaw work together to get to the bottom of this space alien mystery and figure out what this alien is really after: championship rings or giant donuts.

title: The Horrible Herd
description: A heard of supernatural skull cattle wreak havoc on Crystal Cove.

title: The Lost Mines of Kilimanjaro!
description: Driving through Africa, Fred takes a wrong turn at Nairobi on the Mombasa rally race. He drives the gang and the Mystery Machine into some dense jungle in a lost valley at the base of Mount Kilimanjaro. Here, they meet none-other than Jessica Biel, who is climbing Kilimanjaro. She's done it before and loved it so much that she's at it again only from a different approach. But when they get attacked by a twenty-foot tall monster gorilla, they soon have a serious mystery on their hands, one that might lead to the discovery of the legendary lost mines of King Solomon!!!

title: I Put a Hex on You!
description: When Daphne's makeup vlog lands her as the prime consultant to the famous rock band, the Hex Girls, our gang find themselves embroiled in a rockin' mystery involving a cursed guitar that seems to control people's minds. Can our heroes help right this upside-down wrong in time for the band to truly rock for a packed stadium?

title: The Backstage Rage
description: A sinister puppet master manipulates the gang's investigation of a case of counterfeit.

title: The Creeping Creatures
description: A long time ago, there was a town called Gatorburg, where gators flowed wild and free and people got rich. Now, it's a ghost town. Gators are all dried up. But when Scooby and the gang receive an imitation Gatorburg purse, they decide to see for themselves if the gators really are gone. Forced to stay overnight when someone steals the engine to the Mystery Machine, they soon discover that gators have indeed returned - only these have comb-overs, walk on two legs and don't like visitors.

title: A Tiki Scare Is No Fair
description: A Hawaiian vacation turns into another investigation when Scooby and Shaggy are threatened by a witch doctor.

title: The Nightmare Ghost of Psychic U!
description: When the Mystery Inc. gang gets lost in the Pocono Mountains of Pennsylvania, they stumble into Psychic University. They meet Whoopi Goldberg, who's been going to psychic school for a number of months now. She's so close to graduating when a nightmare ghost attacks the school and seems to want to destroy all the students. Can our heroes see their future? Or is it all blank because they don't have one?

title: Protein Titans 2
description: When a mega-successful video game company tries to buy an old algorithm from Velma and convince her to work for them in San Francisco, the gang becomes embroiled in the mystery of a video game villain who has seemingly come to life, the Ghost Chef.

title: Foul Play in Funland
description: The gang investigates a haunted seaside amusement park.

title: Space Station Scooby!
description: When Neil deGrasse Tyson gets trapped on the International Space Station with a horrible monster, Bill Nye arrives to save his good friend with the help of Velma and our mystery solving gang. Arriving at the space station in the nick of time, our heroes work with these two scientific minds to separate the science from the science fiction when a Tardigrade monster wreaks havoc on the ship.

title: Scooby-Doo and the Cyber Chase
description: When Scooby-Doo and the gang try to capture the Phantom Virus, they are accidentally transported into a video game based on their own mystery adventures. While pursuing the Virus through the game's ten outrageous levels, the gang travels from the prehistoric past to the space-age future and even tangles with a hair-raising horde of virtual villains from their most famous capers!

title: Revenge of the Man Crab
description: While hosting a volleyball tournament for Trickell's Triquid diet moisture, a smooth drinking beverage just like water except not so fatty, Crystal Cove beach finds itself attacked by a hideous man crab, who has taken a liking to the tournament's female players. Desperate to stop this beast before it scares away all the tourists, the gang investigates convinced it is a disgruntled local named Skipper Shelton, famous for his delicious clam filled waffle cones, his missing nose and his hatred for Crystal Cove bureaucrats. But when Daphne is captured by the Man Crab, Scooby and the gang have to put the mystery solving into overdrive or risk losing not only Daphne but the sanity of their leader Fred, who is not taking the abduction well.

title: Game of Chicken
description: Fred gets a call for help from Chuck, his daredevil of a best friend, leading the gang on a rescue mission deep in the caverns of an ancient civilization. Once there, they learn of the real mystery: the ghost of the Tribal Warrior still protects the cavern from outsiders!

title: Through the Curtain
description: Traveling through the underground caverns, our heroes trail Pericles and company.

title: A Night of Fright Is No Delight
description: Scooby must spend the night in a haunted house in order to receive an inheritance.

title: In Space
description: A very bad parking choice on Fred's part leads the gang to an asteroid mining base in outer space where an alien virus appears to be infecting the crew one by one, turning them into evil skull-headed aliens. The paranoid, terrified gang must try to solve the mystery before the virus reaches them.

title: Me, Myself and A.I.
description: When an Artificial Intelligence takes over the building of a trendy tech company, the Gang has to solve the computerized mystery and maybe learn a lesson about relying too much on technology.

title: Silver Scream
description: The gang tours an old Hollywood Studio but they soon uncover a mystery concerning the ghost of a silent film comedy star who has returned to make sure his recently discovered final film is never seen.

title: What a Night for a Knight
description: Scooby-Doo and Shaggy stumble across a lone suit of black armor and embark on a quest to find the artifact's missing owner.

title: That's Snow Ghost
description: A ski trip turns spooky for the gang when they run into the ghostly Yeti Beast and a Tibetan hermit, who says he is responsible for summoning the monster.

title: The Hodag of Horror
description: A traveling curio wagon arrives in Crystal Cove and a carnie-barker by the name of Gene Shepherd unveils the Hodag, a beast supposed to be found in the wilds of Wisconsin. It's a horrible fake. But when it comes to life and starts stealing, the gang investigates.

title: Mystery Solvers Club State Finals
description: The Mystery Inc. gang has been invited to compete in the annual Teen Mystery Solver's Convention.

title: A Mystery Solving Gang Divided!
description: Scooby-Doo and the gang travel to Chambersburg, a battlefield near Gettysburg, to investigate the mysterious appearance of ghost zombie Civil War soldiers and come face to face with a rival mystery solving gang, the Funky Phantom crew. The rivalry between the two gangs gets so out of hand that it threatens to keep either group from solving the mystery, until the ghost of Abraham Lincoln appears and tries to get them focused.

title: The New York Underground!
description: Our Shaggy is a bit of a Beatnik poet, and Scooby is so proud that he enters Shaggy into a poetry slam contest in Central Park. But when Shaggy finds out he's going up against famous singer-songwriter Halsey, he just about freaks. He freaks even more when the poetry slam is attacked by a horrible gator-man-monster from the New York City sewers below!

title: World of Witchcraft
description: The gang goes to Salem, Massachusetts for a historical festival, only to discover history repeating itself as a demon has been set loose on the town, supposedly summoned by a witch as revenge for the infamous 17th Century Salem Witch Trials. As the Mayor stirs up fear and paranoia, the whole town goes witch hunt crazy and it's not long before suspicions fall on the gang, in particular, Daphne, who feels empathy for the eccentric, free spirited women accused of witchcraft 350 years ago.

title: A Run Cycle Through Time!
description: When Scooby and the gang accept an invitation from famous actor Malcolm McDowell to take an exploratory trip through time, they find themselves actually traveling into the future. What follows is a strange mystery involving a Malcolm from the future who keeps trying to stop them going any further. Can our gang get to the bottom of this time traveling mystery and save Mr. McDowell from his own invention?

title: Howl of the Fright Hound
description: After a horrible, mechanized beast begins attacking the town, all fingers begin pointing at Scooby. Before the gang can clear his name, the Sheriff has Scooby hauled away to the Crystal Cove Hospital for Criminally Insane Animals. Now, it's up to the gang to clear Scooby's good name. But standing in their way is a new enemy they hadn't counted on: a diabolical parrot named Professor Pericles, who knows more about Mystery Inc. than he should. Add to this the growing friction between Shaggy, Velma and Scooby, and you have a recipe for disaster.

title: Scooby-Doo and the Monster of Mexico
description: Scooby-Doo and the Mystery, Inc. gang are in for a creepy encounter with a monster from Mexico in the mucho spooky, all-new Scooby-Doo movie. The sleuths take a well-earned vacation to visit a friend in Mexico and celebrate the Day of the Dead.

title: Wrath of the Krampus
description: When the strange appearance of a mean goat-man demon named Krampus terrorizes naughty kids all over town, the Mystery Inc. gang decide to look into things. Chasing Krampus all over Crystal Cove, they try to second-guess the crazy, evil goat-man's motives and who could be behind the mystery.

title: Scooby-Doo, Dog Wonder!
description: Scooby-Doo and the gang are on the case of a Medusa Monster that's stealing priceless vases from millionaire art collectors, like Radley Crown and his beloved mutt. What they don't understand is that Radley Crown and his dog are none other than the Blue Falcon and his dog wonder, Dynomutt (who are setting a trap for the Medusa Monster themselves). When our gang's interference causes the Blue Falcon to be taken by the monster, it's up to Dynomutt to put on his Blue Falcon hat and be the brains of the operation. But, he'll need a new Dog Wonder and he picks Scooby-Doo for the job!

title: A Gaggle of Galloping Ghosts
description: The gang visits Franken Castle, which seems to be crowded with famous inhabitants Dracula, the Monster and Wolf Man.

title: Quit Clowning!
description: Shaggy and Scooby take the gang to meet their good friend actor and comedian, Kenan Thompson. He's preparing to broadcast a special one-man show to save a struggling old TV station in Atlanta, Georgia. But when a Ghost Clown attacks, they all freak. It seems that all the many characters Kenan has created for his special one-man show will never see the light of day if the ghost clown has his way.

title: Be Cold, Scooby-Doo!
description: The gang hits the ski slopes, although Daphne's more focused on nailing Fred with a revenge snowball. Their snowy fun is soon interrupted by the appearance of an evil Snowman Monster eager to scare all trespassers off his mountain.

title: Dark Diner of Route 66!
description: Scooby and Shaggy meet up with their biker buddy, Axl Rose, on a tour of famous roadside diners along iconic Route 66. The diner they're heading for is famous for its varieties of delicious pies. But soon, they all find themselves embroiled in a crazy mystery involving spooky mudmen, the lost ruins of an ancient civilization and a treasure of Spanish gold.

title: Gates of Gloom
description: Professor Pericles and what's left of his Mystery Incorporated are looking for the entrance into the caverns, where the cursed treasure and the Evil Entity are buried.

title: A Haunting in Crystal Cove
description: Mayor Jones is under attack by a poltergeist in his own home and the only ones who can help him are the Scooby gang.

title: If You Can't Scooby-Doo the Time, Don't Scooby-Doo the Crime
description: Fred is excited to visit the Vault, a high security prison no convict has ever escaped from. But when the ghost of Stealing Stan, an inmate who always claimed to be innocent, terrorizes the prison, Fred has to solve the mystery and rethink his stance on criminal justice!

title: Scooby-Doo! and the Goblin King
description: To face a Goblin King, courage is crucial. So for Scooby-Doo and Shaggy, the odds are against them!

title: Grand Scam
description: Shaggy takes the Gang to the Minor League Baseball stadium of his youth only to learn that it's about to be shut down because a Ghostly Baseball Player is scaring away the fans and the team! Shaggy puts aside his cowardly ways to saves his home team but will Scooby stand by his, now not so scared, pal?

title: Saga of the Swamp Beast
description: The gang's trip to the bayou is ruined by a shambling Swamp Beast that's scaring away anyone who dares to enter its soggy domain!

title: Hassle in the Castle
description: The sleuths shipwreck on a deserted island and explore a haunted castle.

title: Menace of the Manticore
description: After the Mayor purchases a haunted temple off the internet, Crystal Cove's only theme park, Creepy Spooky Terror Land, is besieged by a Manticore.

title: The Wild Brood
description: A rowdy Orc Biker Gang has decided to roll through Crystal Cove and no one is very happy about it.

title: Aliens Among Us
description: The gang investigates some potential extra-terrestrial life in Crystal Cove with the help of Velma's mother.

title: Scooby's Night with a Frozen Fright
description: Shaggy and Scooby hook a frozen caveman and present the chilly artifact to Oceanland. But the creature is mysteriously thawed out and goes on a rampage.

title: Junkyard Dogs
description: Scooby Doo runs into an old kennel mate from the rescue shelter, Axel, who is now a state-of-the-art, highly trained K-9 police dog. Axel's patronizing attitude towards Scooby makes him and Shaggy determined to be the ones who solve the mystery of the Trash Monster that's been attacking locals at the garbage dump. Meanwhile, in an attempt to better understand Fred, Daphne "becomes" Fred for the day, much to Fred's delight - at first.

title: Now You Sia, Now You Don't!
description: When Daphne gets a call from her good friend singer-songwriter Sia, the gang finds themselves in a mystery involving an evil demon ghost that has taken the shape of Sia as a ghostly doppelganger. And this ghost is getting Sia in hot water by stealing countless gems and jewelry. Can our gang prove her innocence? Can they catch the true thief? Or will the ghostly doppelganger catch them instead?

title: Dead Justice
description: There's a new lawman in town and his name is Dead Justice, an undead cowboy sheriff who used to patrol the streets of Crystal Cove.

title: Fear of the Fire Beast!
description: When Scooby and the gang are in Sicily, they're chasing a fire monster! But, they are surprised to meet up with none other than famous actor Steve Buscemi. His ancestors are from this area, and he has a lot of cousins in town and was just visiting. But, he's being plagued by fire monster attacks. Our gang teams up with Mr. Buscemi to get to the bottom of this fiery mystery. Let's hope Mr. Buscemi can train our gang to be proper fire fighters and mystery solvers, before they all get burned.

title: Web of the Dreamweaver
description: A rash of strange crimes happen when a number of prominent Crystal Cove citizens destroy the things they love most - a car, a house, a food empire. The gang investigates and soon discovers each of these citizens had a dream wherein the Dreamweaver, a horrible goblin-king, told them to do it.

title: The Crown Jewel of Boxing!
description: When Scooby Doo and the mystery solving gang are driving through Louisville, Kentucky, they wind up at the grand opening of a boxing museum created by none other than boxing great Laila Ali. But the museum is under attack from a terrifying robot that seems bent only on destruction. Can the gang and Laila Ali go toe to toe with this metal menace and save the museum? Let's find out! Okay, both contenders of this mystery touch gloves, go to your respective corners and come out swinging!

title: What a Night for a Dark Knight!
description: When Scooby and the gang come to Gotham City to visit Alfred Pennyworth, they stumble into a dangerous mystery! Alfred's been kidnapped by the Man-Bat! Batman is on the case and he does not want any help from our meddling kids.

title: Professor Huh? Part 6 3/4
description: Fred and the gang are called in to help with a mystery involving a figure from Fred's past, Professor Huh? Fred discovers, Rose, his old childhood friend, with whom he learned mystery solving until they had a falling out, has also arrived with her gang. The race to see which gang could solve the mystery first is on, as the rest of the gang learns there's more to this story than meets the eye and Fred's interest in finding Professor Huh? is as personal as it gets.

title: Party Like It's 1899
description: Daphne brings the gang to a Victorian murder mystery party, so they can dress up and solve a fake mystery for once. But when an actual headless count starts actually kidnapping people, the gang must stay in character as they tackle the real caper!

title: When Urkel-Bots Go Bad!
description: When Steve Urkel enlists the help of our mystery solving gang to track down the rampaging Urkel-Bot, they stumble onto a deeper mystery. It seems the Urkel-Bot has gone haywire and escaped a Chicago Museum! The mystery deepens with the appearance of a Technomancer, controlling all the robots! Can our gang and Urkel survive an onslaught of the Technomancer's angry robots? And, more importantly, can our gang survive Urkel?

title: Art of Darkness!
description: World-renowned modern artist Randy Warsaw is Crystal Cove's greatest art treasure. But when Warsaw's greatest work of art, Junk, comes to life and tries to destroy Warsaw, Mayor Nettles asks the gang to investigate.

title: The Movieland Monsters!
description: When the gang helps Carol Burnett beta test her brand new virtual reality Movieland world, they find that the only thing more exciting than being inside some of the most famous movies of all time is being chased by a monster through some of the most famous movies of all time. Can they unravel the mystery of what's gone wrong with Carol's Movieland? Or will the virtual reality unravel our heroes and leave them stranded in there forever.

title: Doo Not Disturb
description: To escape a snowstorm, the gang checks into a creepy, massive hotel run by a man very strict about the hotel rules established by his deceased mother. The gang soon discovers the penalty for breaking the hotel rules is a horrifying scolding from the ghost of the owner's mother.

title: Total Jeopardy!
description: This is Jeopardy! In fact, this is a very special episode of Jeopardy for two reasons. First, Velma and Shaggy are contestants. And second, they're competing against Andy the Brain Bot (a semi-sentient super-smart robot), who's standing at the lecterns with them. Scooby and our gang of mystery solvers are super excited to meet famous TV personality and gameshow host Alex Trebek! But, it's lucky our heroes are on hand because when Velma and Shaggy start outscoring the Brain Bot, it causes the robot to go a little crazy. It threatens to destroy everything if it can't manage to win. Our gang and Mr. Trebek must get to the bottom of who's really behind this robot's dangerous actions, or when they say Final Jeopardy, they really mean it!

title: Peebles' Pet Shop of Terrible Terrors!
description: Scooby and the Mystery Inc. gang meet Wanda Sykes, who is helping save a bunch of cute, fuzzy animals up for adoption in a large pet supply store. When a crazy monster egg hatches a monster in the pet store's back room, our heroes and Wanda must not only save the store and the animals, but their own lives!

title: Kitchen Frightmare
description: Shaggy and Scooby's favorite chef is finally opening his own restaurant but a monstrous Yeti threatens the opening night. The gang has to solve the mystery before dessert is served and Shaggy and Scooby have to resist eating all the food that's meant for the customers!

title: Into the Mouth of Madcap
description: Daphne agrees to watch her friend's kid, Wayne, and convinces Fred to take a night off from mysteries to go to the boardwalk amusement park. Unbeknownst to her, the park is being haunted by a fiendish clown, Madcap.

title: The Man in the Mirror
description: In the basement of a local haunted mansion, the gang finds a strange mirror with a mind of its own.

title: The Scooby of a Thousand Faces!
description: When a marble statue comes to life at a museum in Greece, our gang is caught between a braying minotaur and a sword-wielding Wonder Woman! Teaming up with the Amazonian princess from Themyscira, the Mystery Inc. gang experiences a little rift of boys versus girls. Who can solve this mystery better?

title: Who's Afraid of the Big Bad Werewolf
description: The gang goes camping and stumbles across a lonely graveyard and an empty tomb, whose missing inhabitant was suspected of being a werewolf.

title: The Shrieking Madness
description: With Mystery Inc. broken up, the gang decides to check out life after high school and spend a weekend at Darrow College. But things don't go as planned when a creature called Char Gar Gothakon begins terrorizing the campus. Turns out, this beast is a fictional character come to life. A creation of the author H.P. Hatecraft, who is a professor at the school. Although one of the other professors, Harlan Ellison, claims Hatecraft is a fraud, the creature is definitely real. And when it attacks and carries off Hatecraft to his doom, the gang realizes it has to come together once again to solve this mystery and save Hatecraft's life.

title: Go Away Ghost Ship
description: The gang sets out to solve the mystery of a ghostly pirate seemingly bent on avenging his capture by a shipping magnate's ancestor.

title: Which Witch Is Which?
description: A zombie walks in front of the Mystery Machine as the gang heads into the bayou for a fishing trip, leading to a real witch hunt.

title: Spooky Space Kook
description: The gang stumbles across a UFO's landing site when the Mystery Machine runs out of gas on a deserted road.

title: Don't Fool with a Phantom
description: A phantom interrupts Shaggy and Scooby's performance on a TV dance show.

title: Fright of Hand
description: Fred lives out his childhood dream of being a stage magician as he and the gang go undercover at a private magic club being terrorized by a mutant Rabbit monster.

title: Scooby-Doo in Where's My Mummy?
description: Scooby-Doo and the Mystery Inc. gang become involved in a supernatural mystery in Egypt.

title: One Minute Mysteries!
description: Scooby and Shaggy love hanging out with their very best eating buddy, Barry Allen aka the Flash. Barry is sad his two buddies always get pulled away from their food-fests to go solve mysteries. He decides to help our Mystery Solvers by solving their mysteries Flash-style so quickly our gang can't keep up. Our gang love and respect the Flash but they have a very specific way they like to solve mysteries.

title: Worst in Show
description: After a Giant Houndbeast attacks an elite dog show, the gang goes undercover and enters Scooby in the show in order to solve the mystery.

title: Sorcerer Snacks Scare
description: Shaggy and Scooby discover their new favorite food as the gang investigates the mystery of a frightening Sorcerer that's haunting a snack factory!

title: How to Train Your Coward
description: Finally fed up with monsters and mayhem, Shaggy and Scooby decide to quit the gang and train their replacements in one on-the-job training session, unraveling the mystery of a vampire that's terrorizing a small town.

title: Nowhere to Hyde
description: The gang follows a mysterious figure through a marsh to the house of a latter-day Dr. Jekyll, whose alter ego is apparently a jewel thief.

title: American Goth
description: Shaggy is surprised to see his old childhood first crush has become a Goth. Embarrassed that he hasn't changed at all, Shaggy attends a Goth party with the gang, allowing himself to become initiated into the Goth culture, much to Scooby's concern - especially when the gang discovers there's a ferocious plant monster roaming the corridors of the abandoned hospital the Goth's call home.

title: El Bandito
description: The gang goes to a Day of the Dead festival where they learn the spirit of the legendary criminal, El Bandito, has returned to terrorize the locals. Fred becomes obsessed with solving the mystery and becoming a part of the great legend, himself.

title: Nightmare in Red
description: Our heroes allow themselves to be hypnotized so that they can enter the dreamworld.
